Power BI Dashboard Overview

Power BI was used to visualize churn patterns and translate analytical findings into business insights.

Dashboard Objective
- Identify key churn drivers across customer segments
- Compare churn behavior by tier and billing frequency
- Enable interactive analysis using filters and cross-filtering

KPIs Displayed
- Total Accounts
- Churned Accounts
- Churn Rate (%)

Key Visuals Used
- Tier vs Churn Rate
- Billing Frequency vs Churn Rate
- Seat Range vs Churn Rate
- Satisfaction Level vs Churn Rate
- Support Resolution Time vs Churn Rate
- Churn Reason Distribution

Filters & Interactivity
- Date (Month / Year)
- Tier
- Billing Frequency
- Cross-filtering enabled across all visuals

Analytical Approach
- Churn Rate used as the primary metric for comparison
- Counts used only for supporting context (e.g., churn reasons)
- All visuals are connected to allow drill-down analysis

Outcome
The dashboard enables stakeholders to:
- Quickly identify high-risk customer segments
- Understand churn patterns over time
- Prioritize retention actions based on experience and support quality
